segment.source: Use the following list to help identify errors that are related to sequencing applications by using the command line.
segment.target: Use the following list to help identify errors that are related to sequencing applications by using the command line.

segment.source: You can also see this information by viewing the associated App-V Sequencer log file.
segment.target: You can also see this information by viewing the associated App-V Sequencer log file.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: Multiple errors can occur during sequencing, and if this happens, the error code that is displayed might be the sum of two error codes.
segment.target: Multiple errors can occur during sequencing, and if this happens, the error code that is displayed might be the sum of two error codes.

segment.source: For example, if the /InstallPath and /OutputFile parameters are missing, the App-V Sequencer will return 96—the sum of the two error codes.
segment.target: For example, if the /InstallPath and /OutputFile parameters are missing, the App-V Sequencer will return 96—the sum of the two error codes.
